EXECUTIVE SUMMARY

The Triple-Convergence Revolution

The Quantum Edge Neuromorphic Engine (QENE) represents a fundamental paradigm shift in computing architecture, achieving what was previously considered impossible: the seamless integration of three computing revolutions:

1. Quantum Computing: Exponential parallelism through superposition and entanglement
2. Neuromorphic Engineering: Brain-inspired, event-driven, ultra-efficient computation
3. Edge Intelligence: Distributed, real-time processing at the data source

This convergence enables quantum-enhanced neuromorphic intelligence that operates within the extreme constraints of edge environments while maintaining quantum advantages. QENE achieves energy efficiency improvements of 10-100× over existing edge AI systems while delivering quantum advantages in learning speed, robustness, and problem-solving capabilities.

Key Breakthroughs

1. Quantum-Neural State Encoding (QNSE): Unified representation bridging quantum and neural computation
2. Energy-Quantum Uncertainty Principle: Formal optimization framework balancing energy consumption and quantum uncertainty
3. Quantum-Enhanced STDP (Qe-STDP): Novel learning rule leveraging quantum correlations for accelerated learning
4. Hyper-Dimensional Quantum Memory (HDQM): Scalable associative memory with quantum superposition capabilities
5. Heterogeneous 3D Integration: Practical implementation combining cryogenic quantum and room-temperature neuromorphic components

Performance Targets

Metric Target Current State-of-Art Improvement
Energy per Inference <1 mJ 10-100 mJ 10-100×
Inference Latency (p95) <20 ms 50-200 ms 2.5-10×
Quantum Advantage >2× speedup N/A New capability
Model Accuracy >95% 90-95% 5-10% absolute
Operating Temperature -40°C to +85°C 0°C to 70°C Extended range

