3. HARDWARE ARCHITECTURE

3.1 Heterogeneous 3D Integration

3.1.1 Layer Stacking Architecture

QENE employs a novel 3D stacking approach:

```
Layer 1: Quantum Processor (10 mK)
  - Superconducting transmon qubits (8-16 physical)
  - Microwave resonators and control lines
  - Josephson junction arrays
  
Layer 2: Quantum Control (4 K)
  - Cryogenic CMOS for initial amplification
  - HEMT amplifiers
  - Initial signal conditioning
  
Layer 3: Neuromorphic Processor (77 K)
  - Memristive crossbar arrays (1024×1024)
  - CMOS neuron circuits
  - STDP plasticity engines
  
Layer 4: Classical Processor (300 K)
  - ARM Cortex-A78AE CPU
  - FPGA for real-time control
  - Power management IC
  - I/O interfaces
```

3.1.2 Thermal Management

Innovative thermal management techniques enable this integration:

1. Microfluidic cooling: Liquid nitrogen channels between layers
2. Aerogel insulation: Ultralow thermal conductivity isolation
3. Selective thermal vias: Controlled heat extraction paths
4. Pulse tube cryocoolers: 10 mK to 300 K temperature gradient

3.1.3 Interconnect Technology

High-density interconnects enable communication between layers:

1. Through-silicon vias (TSVs): 1,000,000 vias/cm² density
2. Superconducting interconnects: NbTiN lines with <1 mΩ resistance
3. Quantum-limited amplifiers: Josephson parametric amplifiers for quantum signals
4. Optical interconnects: Silicon photonics for layer 3-4 communication

3.2 Quantum Processor Specifications

3.2.1 Qubit Architecture

```
Technology: Superconducting transmon
Number of qubits: 8-16 physical, 2-4 logical (with error mitigation)
Connectivity: All-to-all via tunable couplers
Frequency: 4-8 GHz range
Anharmonicity: -200 to -300 MHz
T1 time: >100 μs (target)
T2 time: >50 μs (target)
Readout fidelity: >98%
Gate fidelity: >99.5% (single-qubit), >98.5% (two-qubit)
```

3.2.2 Control Electronics

```
DAC channels: 16, 14-bit resolution, 2 GSa/s
ADC channels: 8, 12-bit resolution, 1 GSa/s
Local oscillators: 8 phase-locked sources
Digital controller: Xilinx Zynq UltraScale+ RFSoC
Interface: PCIe 4.0 x8, 10 Gb Ethernet
```

3.2.3 Cryogenic System

```
Platform: Dilution refrigerator
Base temperature: 10 mK
Cooling power: 10 μW at 100 mK
Cooldown time: 48 hours
Hold time: 30 days
Power consumption: 5 kW (room temperature)
```

3.3 Neuromorphic Processor Specifications

3.3.1 Core Architecture

```
Neuron count: 1,024-65,536
Synapse count: 1,000,000-100,000,000
Neuron model: Leaky integrate-and-fire (LIF) with adaptation
Synapse model: Memristive with STDP plasticity
Crossbar size: 1024×1024 configurable
Weight precision: 4-8 bits
Spike timing resolution: 1 μs
Event throughput: 1 billion events/second
```

3.3.2 Memristive Technology

```
Memristor type: HfO₂ or TaOₓ
Cell size: 4F² (F = feature size)
Resistance range: 10 kΩ - 10 MΩ
Switching voltage: ±1-2 V
Switching time: <10 ns
Endurance: >10¹² cycles
Retention: >10 years
```

3.3.3 Energy Efficiency

```
Static power: 1 nW/neuron
Spike energy: 10 pJ/spike
Synaptic event: 1 pJ/event
Read energy: 0.1 pJ/bit
Write energy: 1 pJ/bit
Total power: 1-100 mW typical
```

3.4 Classical Processor Specifications

3.4.1 Compute Resources

```
CPU: ARM Cortex-A78AE (8 cores, 2.8 GHz)
GPU: ARM Mali-G78 (optional)
NPU: Ethos-N78 (8 TOPS at INT8)
FPGA: Xilinx Zynq UltraScale+ (154K logic cells)
Memory: 8 GB LPDDR5, 256 GB UFS 3.1 storage
Interfaces: PCIe 4.0, USB 3.2, Ethernet, CAN, SPI, I2C
```

3.4.2 Power Management

```
Power sources: 3.3 V main, energy harvesting inputs
Power management: Dynamic voltage/frequency scaling
Energy harvesting: Solar, thermal, vibration, RF
Energy storage: Supercapacitor (10 J), Li-ion battery (100 Wh/kg)
Power gating: Fine-grained domain control
```

