4.3 Development Tools

4.3.1 QENE SDK

Comprehensive SDK for application development:

```python
# Example: Quantum-enhanced neural network
import qene

# Create quantum-enhanced network
network = qene.QENeuralNetwork(
    layers=[1024, 512, 256, 10],
    neuron_model='quantum_lif',
    quantum_enhancement=True
)

# Train with Qe-STDP
trainer = qene.QeSTDPTrainer(
    learning_rate=0.01,
    quantum_factor=0.3
)

# Optimize for edge deployment
optimized_model = qene.optimize_for_edge(
    network,
    target_device='qene-edge-v3',
    constraints={'energy': '1mJ', 'latency': '20ms'}
)
```

4.3.2 Simulation Environment

High-fidelity simulation for development and testing:

```
Components:
  • Quantum simulator: Qiskit Aer, Pennylane
  • Neuromorphic simulator: Brian2, NEST
  • Hardware-in-the-loop: Real hardware interfacing
  • Performance modeling: Energy, latency, accuracy prediction

Capabilities:
  • Full-system simulation
  • Hardware-accurate timing
  • Energy consumption modeling
  • Fault injection testing
```

4.3.3 Deployment Tools

Tools for deploying to edge devices:

```bash
# Deploy model to edge device
qene deploy model.pb --target qene-edge-01 \
  --optimize-level 3 \
  --energy-budget 1mJ \
  --verify-security

# Monitor deployed system
qene monitor qene-edge-01 \
  --metrics energy,latency,accuracy \
  --alert-thresholds energy>2mJ,latency>25ms

# Update firmware over-the-air
qene ota-update qene-edge-01 firmware-v3.1.bin \
  --validate-signature \
  --backup-state
```

